text: The vermiculated spinefoot (Siganus vermiculatus), also known as maze rabbitfish, is a species of rabbitfish. Like all rabbitfishes, it has venomous spines on the dorsal, anal, and pelvic fins. It is reef associated fish species that inhabit waters at depths from . The maximum length is .
